'''Berk''' is a [[slang]] term derived from [[Cockney rhyming slang]]. It is a shortened version of [[Berkeley Hunt]], the [[hunting with hounds|hunt]] based at [[Berkeley Castle]] in [[Gloucestershire]]. In the rhyming slang, "hunt" is made to rhyme with [[cunt]] giving the word berk its original slang meaning.<ref>[[Chambers Dictionary]]: Entry for berk</ref>  It is not perceived to be excessively rude, perhaps because whilst it is known for being a slang word, its real meaning is not well known. Similar to [[Charlie Hunt]] as in "he's a right Charlie" another [[Cockney]] saying - Charlie Hunt being a local [[East End of London| east end]] figure of the time this saying was common.

It is also, perhaps more commonly, used to mean [[idiot]], in an affectionate sense.

In danish, the word "berk" means someone who thinks he/she is good. It is slang and it is not used by many in Denmark. You can not find the word in any danish dictionary, but it used by smaller subcultures in Denmark. You can use the word in a sentence like "now don't think you are good, your berk!".